Adult.description: Bohemian Waxwings have gray bellies and rich cinnamon under the tail whereas Cedar Waxwings have yellowish bellies and white under the tail. Perched birds have a white bar across the dark wing feathers that Cedar Waxwings lack.

Breeding adult.description: European Starlings could be confused with Cedar Waxwings in flight, but starlings have a darker belly and do not have yellow-tipped tail feathers like Cedar Waxwings.
